					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentary. It seems to record some provision made for food to be distributed to certain Sundaranāchchi, out of the food given to certain Pendāṭṭiyār, according to the royal order.</p>						

						<p>Second piece connected with the gift of land for making procession of the deity and for food offerings in the festival of <hi rend="italic">Māsimagam</hi> in every year. All the fragments belong to the 13th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
